<script>
"use strict";
var positionImage = function positionImage(imageEl) {
var imageDimensions = imageEl.dataset.imageDimensions.split('x');
var originalWidth = imageDimensions[0];
var originalHeight = imageDimensions[1];
var focalPoint = imageEl.dataset.imageFocalPoint.split(',');
var focalPointX = focalPoint[0];
var focalPointY = focalPoint[1];
var parentNode = imageEl.parentNode;
var scale = function () {
var imageRatio = originalWidth / originalHeight;
var parentClientSize = {
height: parentNode.clientHeight,
width: parentNode.clientWidth
};
var parentRatio = parentClientSize.width / parentClientSize.height;
if (imageRatio > parentRatio) {
return parentClientSize.height / originalHeight;
}
return parentClientSize.width / originalWidth;
}();
var getRelativeOffset = function getRelativeOffset() {
var targetWidth = Math.ceil(originalWidth * scale);
var targetHeight = Math.ceil(originalHeight * scale);
var parentDimensionWidth = parentNode.offsetWidth;
var parentDimensionHeight = parentNode.offsetHeight;
var overflowWidth = targetWidth - parentDimensionWidth;
var overflowHeight = targetHeight - parentDimensionHeight;
var valueX;
if (overflowWidth === 0) {
valueX = focalPointX;
} else {
valueX = Math.max(Math.min(targetWidth * focalPointX - parentDimensionWidth * 0.5, overflowWidth), 0) / overflowWidth;
}
var valueY;
if (overflowHeight === 0) {
valueY = focalPointY;
} else {
valueY = Math.max(Math.min(targetHeight * focalPointY - parentDimensionHeight * 0.5, overflowHeight), 0) / overflowHeight;
}
return {
valueX: valueX,
valueY: valueY
};
};
var relativeOffset = getRelativeOffset();
var valueX = relativeOffset.valueX;
var valueY = relativeOffset.valueY;
imageEl.style.objectPosition = "".concat(valueX * 100, "% ").concat(valueY * 100, "%");
Object.assign(imageEl.style, {
height: '100%',
width: '100%',
objectFit: 'cover',
});
};
</script>

<h2 style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><span class="sqsrte-text-highlight" data-text-attribute-id="d56c8309-f988-4a10-985d-a862a259642b">The Problem</span></h2><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="sqsrte-large">Bacterial infections are a major public health concern and the second leading cause of death. By 2050, projections suggest 10 million people a year could die from previously treatable bacterial infections - more than triple the death toll of COVID-19 in 2020. Alternative prevention and treatment strategies are urgently needed to prevent a global health crisis.</p>

<h2 style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><span class="sqsrte-text-highlight" data-text-attribute-id="291c00b0-681f-40d3-b95b-0e773da7db56">Our Solution</span></h2><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="sqsrte-large">Our idea is to create a multivalent subunit vaccine containing peptidoglycan, lipopolysaccharides (LPS), and lipoteichoic acid (LTAs), which will stimulate an immune response against both gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria. This immune response will generate specific antibodies and cytotoxic T cells that can effectively target and kill the bacteria.</p>

<script>
"use strict";
var positionImage = function positionImage(imageEl) {
var imageDimensions = imageEl.dataset.imageDimensions.split('x');
var originalWidth = imageDimensions[0];
var originalHeight = imageDimensions[1];
var focalPoint = imageEl.dataset.imageFocalPoint.split(',');
var focalPointX = focalPoint[0];
var focalPointY = focalPoint[1];
var parentNode = imageEl.parentNode;
var scale = function () {
var imageRatio = originalWidth / originalHeight;
var parentClientSize = {
height: parentNode.clientHeight,
width: parentNode.clientWidth
};
var parentRatio = parentClientSize.width / parentClientSize.height;
if (imageRatio > parentRatio) {
return parentClientSize.height / originalHeight;
}
return parentClientSize.width / originalWidth;
}();
var getRelativeOffset = function getRelativeOffset() {
var targetWidth = Math.ceil(originalWidth * scale);
var targetHeight = Math.ceil(originalHeight * scale);
var parentDimensionWidth = parentNode.offsetWidth;
var parentDimensionHeight = parentNode.offsetHeight;
var overflowWidth = targetWidth - parentDimensionWidth;
var overflowHeight = targetHeight - parentDimensionHeight;
var valueX;
if (overflowWidth === 0) {
valueX = focalPointX;
} else {
valueX = Math.max(Math.min(targetWidth * focalPointX - parentDimensionWidth * 0.5, overflowWidth), 0) / overflowWidth;
}
var valueY;
if (overflowHeight === 0) {
valueY = focalPointY;
} else {
valueY = Math.max(Math.min(targetHeight * focalPointY - parentDimensionHeight * 0.5, overflowHeight), 0) / overflowHeight;
}
return {
valueX: valueX,
valueY: valueY
};
};
var relativeOffset = getRelativeOffset();
var valueX = relativeOffset.valueX;
var valueY = relativeOffset.valueY;
imageEl.style.objectPosition = "".concat(valueX * 100, "% ").concat(valueY * 100, "%");
Object.assign(imageEl.style, {
height: '100%',
width: '100%',
objectFit: 'cover',
});
};
</script>

<script>
"use strict";
var positionImage = function positionImage(imageEl) {
var imageDimensions = imageEl.dataset.imageDimensions.split('x');
var originalWidth = imageDimensions[0];
var originalHeight = imageDimensions[1];
var focalPoint = imageEl.dataset.imageFocalPoint.split(',');
var focalPointX = focalPoint[0];
var focalPointY = focalPoint[1];
var parentNode = imageEl.parentNode;
var scale = function () {
var imageRatio = originalWidth / originalHeight;
var parentClientSize = {
height: parentNode.clientHeight,
width: parentNode.clientWidth
};
var parentRatio = parentClientSize.width / parentClientSize.height;
if (imageRatio > parentRatio) {
return parentClientSize.height / originalHeight;
}
return parentClientSize.width / originalWidth;
}();
var getRelativeOffset = function getRelativeOffset() {
var targetWidth = Math.ceil(originalWidth * scale);
var targetHeight = Math.ceil(originalHeight * scale);
var parentDimensionWidth = parentNode.offsetWidth;
var parentDimensionHeight = parentNode.offsetHeight;
var overflowWidth = targetWidth - parentDimensionWidth;
var overflowHeight = targetHeight - parentDimensionHeight;
var valueX;
if (overflowWidth === 0) {
valueX = focalPointX;
} else {
valueX = Math.max(Math.min(targetWidth * focalPointX - parentDimensionWidth * 0.5, overflowWidth), 0) / overflowWidth;
}
var valueY;
if (overflowHeight === 0) {
valueY = focalPointY;
} else {
valueY = Math.max(Math.min(targetHeight * focalPointY - parentDimensionHeight * 0.5, overflowHeight), 0) / overflowHeight;
}
return {
valueX: valueX,
valueY: valueY
};
};
var relativeOffset = getRelativeOffset();
var valueX = relativeOffset.valueX;
var valueY = relativeOffset.valueY;
imageEl.style.objectPosition = "".concat(valueX * 100, "% ").concat(valueY * 100, "%");
Object.assign(imageEl.style, {
height: '100%',
width: '100%',
objectFit: 'cover',
});
};
</script>

<script>
"use strict";
var positionImage = function positionImage(imageEl) {
var imageDimensions = imageEl.dataset.imageDimensions.split('x');
var originalWidth = imageDimensions[0];
var originalHeight = imageDimensions[1];
var focalPoint = imageEl.dataset.imageFocalPoint.split(',');
var focalPointX = focalPoint[0];
var focalPointY = focalPoint[1];
var parentNode = imageEl.parentNode;
var scale = function () {
var imageRatio = originalWidth / originalHeight;
var parentClientSize = {
height: parentNode.clientHeight,
width: parentNode.clientWidth
};
var parentRatio = parentClientSize.width / parentClientSize.height;
if (imageRatio > parentRatio) {
return parentClientSize.height / originalHeight;
}
return parentClientSize.width / originalWidth;
}();
var getRelativeOffset = function getRelativeOffset() {
var targetWidth = Math.ceil(originalWidth * scale);
var targetHeight = Math.ceil(originalHeight * scale);
var parentDimensionWidth = parentNode.offsetWidth;
var parentDimensionHeight = parentNode.offsetHeight;
var overflowWidth = targetWidth - parentDimensionWidth;
var overflowHeight = targetHeight - parentDimensionHeight;
var valueX;
if (overflowWidth === 0) {
valueX = focalPointX;
} else {
valueX = Math.max(Math.min(targetWidth * focalPointX - parentDimensionWidth * 0.5, overflowWidth), 0) / overflowWidth;
}
var valueY;
if (overflowHeight === 0) {
valueY = focalPointY;
} else {
valueY = Math.max(Math.min(targetHeight * focalPointY - parentDimensionHeight * 0.5, overflowHeight), 0) / overflowHeight;
}
return {
valueX: valueX,
valueY: valueY
};
};
var relativeOffset = getRelativeOffset();
var valueX = relativeOffset.valueX;
var valueY = relativeOffset.valueY;
imageEl.style.objectPosition = "".concat(valueX * 100, "% ").concat(valueY * 100, "%");
Object.assign(imageEl.style, {
height: '100%',
width: '100%',
objectFit: 'cover',
});
};
</script>

<script>
"use strict";
var positionImage = function positionImage(imageEl) {
var imageDimensions = imageEl.dataset.imageDimensions.split('x');
var originalWidth = imageDimensions[0];
var originalHeight = imageDimensions[1];
var focalPoint = imageEl.dataset.imageFocalPoint.split(',');
var focalPointX = focalPoint[0];
var focalPointY = focalPoint[1];
var parentNode = imageEl.parentNode;
var scale = function () {
var imageRatio = originalWidth / originalHeight;
var parentClientSize = {
height: parentNode.clientHeight,
width: parentNode.clientWidth
};
var parentRatio = parentClientSize.width / parentClientSize.height;
if (imageRatio > parentRatio) {
return parentClientSize.height / originalHeight;
}
return parentClientSize.width / originalWidth;
}();
var getRelativeOffset = function getRelativeOffset() {
var targetWidth = Math.ceil(originalWidth * scale);
var targetHeight = Math.ceil(originalHeight * scale);
var parentDimensionWidth = parentNode.offsetWidth;
var parentDimensionHeight = parentNode.offsetHeight;
var overflowWidth = targetWidth - parentDimensionWidth;
var overflowHeight = targetHeight - parentDimensionHeight;
var valueX;
if (overflowWidth === 0) {
valueX = focalPointX;
} else {
valueX = Math.max(Math.min(targetWidth * focalPointX - parentDimensionWidth * 0.5, overflowWidth), 0) / overflowWidth;
}
var valueY;
if (overflowHeight === 0) {
valueY = focalPointY;
} else {
valueY = Math.max(Math.min(targetHeight * focalPointY - parentDimensionHeight * 0.5, overflowHeight), 0) / overflowHeight;
}
return {
valueX: valueX,
valueY: valueY
};
};
var relativeOffset = getRelativeOffset();
var valueX = relativeOffset.valueX;
var valueY = relativeOffset.valueY;
imageEl.style.objectPosition = "".concat(valueX * 100, "% ").concat(valueY * 100, "%");
Object.assign(imageEl.style, {
height: '100%',
width: '100%',
objectFit: 'cover',
});
};
</script>

<script>
"use strict";
var positionImage = function positionImage(imageEl) {
var imageDimensions = imageEl.dataset.imageDimensions.split('x');
var originalWidth = imageDimensions[0];
var originalHeight = imageDimensions[1];
var focalPoint = imageEl.dataset.imageFocalPoint.split(',');
var focalPointX = focalPoint[0];
var focalPointY = focalPoint[1];
var parentNode = imageEl.parentNode;
var scale = function () {
var imageRatio = originalWidth / originalHeight;
var parentClientSize = {
height: parentNode.clientHeight,
width: parentNode.clientWidth
};
var parentRatio = parentClientSize.width / parentClientSize.height;
if (imageRatio > parentRatio) {
return parentClientSize.height / originalHeight;
}
return parentClientSize.width / originalWidth;
}();
var getRelativeOffset = function getRelativeOffset() {
var targetWidth = Math.ceil(originalWidth * scale);
var targetHeight = Math.ceil(originalHeight * scale);
var parentDimensionWidth = parentNode.offsetWidth;
var parentDimensionHeight = parentNode.offsetHeight;
var overflowWidth = targetWidth - parentDimensionWidth;
var overflowHeight = targetHeight - parentDimensionHeight;
var valueX;
if (overflowWidth === 0) {
valueX = focalPointX;
} else {
valueX = Math.max(Math.min(targetWidth * focalPointX - parentDimensionWidth * 0.5, overflowWidth), 0) / overflowWidth;
}
var valueY;
if (overflowHeight === 0) {
valueY = focalPointY;
} else {
valueY = Math.max(Math.min(targetHeight * focalPointY - parentDimensionHeight * 0.5, overflowHeight), 0) / overflowHeight;
}
return {
valueX: valueX,
valueY: valueY
};
};
var relativeOffset = getRelativeOffset();
var valueX = relativeOffset.valueX;
var valueY = relativeOffset.valueY;
imageEl.style.objectPosition = "".concat(valueX * 100, "% ").concat(valueY * 100, "%");
Object.assign(imageEl.style, {
height: '100%',
width: '100%',
objectFit: 'cover',
});
};
</script>

</div></div></div><div class="fe-block fe-block-c3ff99130d8b258625df"><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html sqs-background-enabled" data-block-type="2" id="block-c3ff99130d8b258625df"><div class="sqs-block-content">
<h2 style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><strong>Immune Recognition</strong></h2><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">When peptidoglycan is detected by the immune system, it triggers an immune response that involves the production of cytokines and chemokines. These signalling molecules help to activate immune cells, such as macrophages and dendritic cells, which can engulf and destroy bacteria.</p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Peptidoglycan also activates specific cells of the immune system, such as T cells, which can recognize and kill infected cells. The inclusion of peptidoglycan as an antigen in a vaccine can help to stimulate an immune response that targets bacterial infections.</p>
<style>
#block-c3ff99130d8b258625df.sqs-block.sqs-background-enabled {
box-sizing: border-box;
height: 100%;
padding: 10% 10% 10% 10%;
border-radius: 0px 0px 0px 0px;
}
</style>
</div></div></div><div class="fe-block fe-block-a97908108729df727a4c"><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html sqs-background-enabled" data-block-type="2" id="block-a97908108729df727a4c"><div class="sqs-block-content">
<h2 style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"><strong>Broad Coverage</strong></h2><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="">Peptidoglycan is recognized by the immune system as a pathogen-associated molecular pattern (PAMP) and can trigger an immune response. It has the potential to be used as an antigen in a vaccine against bacterial infections. A multivalent vaccine containing peptidoglycan, LPS, and LTAs can provide broad protection against a range of bacterial infections by targeting multiple components of the bacterial cell wall.</p><p class="" data-rte-preserve-empty="true" style="white-space:pre-wrap;"></p>
<style>
#block-a97908108729df727a4c.sqs-block.sqs-background-enabled {
box-sizing: border-box;
height: 100%;
padding: 10% 10% 10% 10%;
border-radius: 0px 0px 0px 0px;

<p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">A multivalent subunit vaccine containing peptidoglycan, LPS, and LTAs targets multiple components of the bacterial cell wall, providing broad protection against gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">This vaccine can stimulate a comprehensive immune response, reducing the incidence and severity of bacterial infections, leading to significant public health benefits.</p>
